Conclusion
Prompt engineering is an essential skill for interacting with AI. Zero-Shot is useful for straightforward tasks, One-Shot provides guidance through a single example, and Few-Shot improves consistency using multiple examples. Selecting the right technique leads to more accurate and reliable AI-generated outputs.

